The paper focuses on improving the accuracy of predictive models based on machine learning by automatically detecting and repairing data errors, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DB (Databases), as the paper deals with data quality issues. The paper also uses deep learning models for error detection, which suggests a possible sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses optimization techniques for improving the speed of error detection and repair, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.SE (Software Engineering).
